data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_033b23e11e4f0dbd0069b34945d338819499c69c29ad262343","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":65,"text":"In the 2024 Summer Olympics held in Paris (from July 26 to August 11, 2024), the United States achieved a **total of 126 medals**, placing them at the top of the medal standings. This included:\n\n- **40 Gold medals**  \n- **44 Silver medals**  \n- **42 Bronze medals** ([teamusa.com](https://www.teamusa.com/paris-2024/olympics/medals))\n\nLeading global sports authorities such as ESPN and official sources confirm these totals:\n\n- ESPN's “2024 Paris Olympic Medal Tracker” shows Team USA with 40 gold, 44 silver, and 42 bronze—summing to 126 medals, ranking highest overall ([espn.com](https://www.espn.com/olympics/summer/2024/medals)).  \n- Statista similarly reports the same breakdown and total for Team USA ([statista.com](https://www.statista.com/statistics/1483973/medals-olympic-summer-games-paris-2024/)).\n\nTherefore, **the United States won a total of 126 medals** at the 2024 Summer Olympics.\n\nIf you'd like further details—such as medal distribution by sport, standout athletes, or how Team USA compared to other nations like China—feel free to ask!"}

